OL,6,FSince the accident, Paul's brain still
OL,7,Fsometimes stops sending signals to his
OL,8,Flegs, which will stop working from
OL,9,F"anywhere from a minute to an hour".
OL,11,FHe also now lives with constant
OL,12,Fmigraine pressure, post-traumatic
OL,13,Fstress disorder and depression.
OL,15,FLouise Aubrey, community development
OL,16,Fmanager at Brain Tumour Research,
OL,17,Fsaid: "Paul is an extraordinary person
OL,18,Fand a true inspiration to us all.
